          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`Path::is_file()` treats more than a missing file as false, including dangling symlinks, directories, and unreadable paths. This change turns those corruption cases into silent skips, so a broken `plan.md` will no longer surface as a verify failure. If the intent is only to skip when the file is truly absent, the check needs to distinguish `NotFound` from other states.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "/home/flip451/individual/t-rust/templates/SoTOHE-core/libs/infrastructure/src/verify/view_freshness.rs",
              "line": 89,
              "category": "error_handling"
            }
          ],
          "hash": "rvw1:sha256:fe2fdeef1d11acc9479885342676fa430589b2f5db5d4ff024ba1c7bd062fa1c",
          "at": "2026-04-27T04:51:27Z"
        },
        {
          "type": "fast",
          "verdict": "findings_remain",
          "findings": [
            {
              "message": "`Path::is_file()` is broader than \"plan.md is absent\": it also returns false for dangling symlinks and some filesystem errors, so this `continue` now silently skips corrupted `plan.md` states instead of surfacing a finding. The skip should only apply after confirming the file is genuinely missing, matching the absent-vs-corrupted split used in `validate_track_snapshots`.",
              "severity": "P1",
              "file": "libs/infrastructure/src/verify/view_freshness.rs",
              "line": 89,
              "category": "logic"
            }
          ],
